 Group 1: Optimistic Locking in mutate() — Fixes #1, #2, #4, #11

 Root cause: mutate('local', updater) clones in-memory this.state, applies the updater, writes to localStorage + broadcasts. If two tabs read the same state simultaneously, both
  produce seq: N+1 and overwrite each other.

 File: packages/sdk/src/sessionCoordinator.ts — mutate() (lines 1108-1124)

 Change: Re-read localStorage at the start of every local mutation. If the persisted state has a higher seq, merge it before applying the updater:

 private mutate(source: 'local' | 'remote', updater: (draft: SharedSessionState) => void): void {
   // NEW: Re-read from localStorage before local mutations (optimistic locking)
   if (source === 'local') {
     try {
       const raw = window.localStorage.getItem(this.key);
       if (raw) {
         const persisted = sanitizeSharedState(JSON.parse(raw), this.siteId, this.sessionId);
         if (persisted.seq > this.state.seq ||
             (persisted.seq === this.state.seq && persisted.updatedAt > this.state.updatedAt)) {
           this.state = persisted;
         }
       }
     } catch { /* ignore */ }
   }

   const draft = sanitizeSharedState(this.state, this.siteId, this.sessionId);
   updater(draft);
   draft.seq = Math.max(1, Number(draft.seq) || 1) + (source === 'local' ? 1 : 0);
   draft.updatedAt = now();
   this.state = draft;
   // ... rest unchanged
 }

 This also fixes #2 (LogicalTabId race): two tabs reading the same nextLogicalTabId is prevented because the second tab will re-read and see the first tab's increment.

 Additionally, add duplicate logicalTabId detection in sanitizeSharedState() (line 309-311):

 // After existing nextLogicalTabId recalc, add dedup:
 const seenTabIds = new Set<number>();
 state.tabs = state.tabs.filter(tab => {
   if (seenTabIds.has(tab.logicalTabId)) return false;
   seenTabIds.add(tab.logicalTabId);
   return true;
 });
 if (state.nextLogicalTabId <= (state.tabs.at(-1)?.logicalTabId ?? 0)) {
   state.nextLogicalTabId = state.tabs.reduce((max, tab) => Math.max(max, tab.logicalTabId), 0) + 1;
 }

