 Group 4: Visitor ID Resilience — Fixes #3, #9, #10, #13

 File: packages/sdk/src/index.ts — resolveVisitorId() (lines 307-355)

 Fix #3 & #9: Sync visitor ID to ALL available stores

 Problem: When ID is loaded from one store (e.g., cookie), it's only synced to localStorage. Not synced to sessionStorage. When loaded from localStorage, not synced to
 sessionStorage.

 Change: After resolving the visitor ID from any source, persist to all three stores:

 function resolveVisitorId(cfg: RoverInit): string | undefined {
   // ... existing resolution logic (cookie → localStorage → sessionStorage → generate) ...

   // NEW: After resolving `result`, ensure it's in all available stores
   if (result) {
     syncVisitorIdToAllStores(cfg.siteId, result);
   }
   return result;
 }

 function syncVisitorIdToAllStores(siteId: string, visitorId: string): void {
   const key = `${VISITOR_ID_PREFIX}${siteId}`;
   try { window.localStorage.setItem(key, visitorId); } catch { /* ignore */ }
   try { window.sessionStorage.setItem(key, visitorId); } catch { /* ignore */ }
   persistVisitorIdCookie(siteId, visitorId);
 }

 This ensures that once resolved, the ID is available from all fallback paths. Addresses #10 (session ID derivation) transitively since session ID = hash(siteId:visitorId).

 Fix #13: Cookie domain fragmentation

 The current code already tries broadest domain first (candidateCookieDomains returns .example.com before .sub.example.com). The only gap is documentation. No code change needed
